  • High Accuracy & Fast Refresh Data: With this smart sensor, the PM2.5 accuracy is 15 g/m while temperature and humidity accuracies are 0.54F and 3%RH.The two-second correction data feature shows the latest changes in PM2.5, temperature, and humidity.
  • Multifunctional Air Quality Detector: The GoveeLife Air Quality Monitor conveniently measures 3 important indexes for indoor air quality, including PM2.5, temperature, and humidity.
  • Switchable Display: Press the top button for the clock & PM2.5 display. Long press for 2 seconds to switch to bright screen mode & night mode. The LED indicator displays 4 levels of ambient air quality. 2.4G Wi-Fi is required to display the time.
  • Connect with GoveeHome Appliances: Set your target air quality and link with your other GoveeHome smart appliances. GoveeLife air purifiers, humidifiers, and space heaters will turn on and off automatically when the indoor air quality changes.
  • Free Data Storage & Export: Enjoy remote monitoring with the air quality monitor via Bluetooth or Wi-Fi, including online viewing of 13-day data graphs and exporting data over the past 2 years. No built-in battery. Uses type-C cables only.
  • NOTE: H5106 Supports GoveeLife Appliances: Smart Air Purifier-H7126,H7120,H7124,H712C,H7122,H7123Humidifiers-H7140; Fans-H7100, H7102

  • Joseph T.
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Great Air Monitor w/ Smart Home Integration Features
    Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2024
    Overall, this is a great air monitor for the money and I love the smart home integration and automation you can setup if you have other Govee products. I bought 2 Govee HEPA air purifiers, one for my downstairs, and one for our master bedroom. I also bought 2 of... See more
    Overall, this is a great air monitor for the money and I love the smart home integration and automation you can setup if you have other Govee products.

    I bought 2 Govee HEPA air purifiers, one for my downstairs, and one for our master bedroom. I also bought 2 of these air monitors (even though the air purifiers also have their own PM 2.5 sensors). For the downstairs, I placed one of the monitors on the other side of the house and have automations so that if air quality dips in that room, it can still trigger my Govee HEPA air purifier on the same level into high mode to help purifier and circulate the air quicker along the ~1,250 sqft area. Once healthier air quality conditions are met I can also set an automation to put the HEPA filter back down to auto / low.

    The temperature readings are fairly accurate out of the box, and youre able to make adjustments if needed. I also have a Govee space heater that unfortunately cant automatically turn on or off to maintain a set temperature, but with this sensor and automation, I can set commands to automatically turn on or off the space heater to keep the room within a set temperature range.

    The unit also shows humidity, which is also very important for indoor air quality and health. Ive learned that in some rooms or conditions my humidity can get a bit higher than ideal in warmer weather or after a shower in our master bathroom. Ive been managing that now by leaving on the bathroom ventilation longer than I would have previously. But Im also looking into adding Govee humidifiers and dehumidifiers to help manage it more closely and also be able to take advantage of smart home automation to handle that as well.

    The only thing I was a little disappointed with is that it doesnt monitor other key air quality metrics that some other brands offer (VOCs, PM10, CO2, etc), and would be great if these could also double as carbon monoxide or combustible gas detectors. However, given the price point, Im sure if they offered these features the units would be a bit more expensive.

    Given that, I was torn on trying to decide between eating this 4 or 5 stars (I would rate it 4.5 if given the option by Amazon), but ultimately, given the price vs features and performance it does have, I think a 5 star rating is still fair and justifiable.
